rComments: Amazing professor lesson plan was well thought out with 5 central themes to all the readings in the course. u learn a lot with him and he's very inspiring, he's really good at captivating his audience. He is particular about spelling and grammer. Don't miss class! He gives u a ton of info in class. this course is all essays and one presentation

- his Anglican leanings are entirely evident, suggested that we all should have the same amount of confidence as a classroom of well-dressed students that he had visited at a rich, private school, marking seems to be arbitrary and when questioned about comments written on essays, doesn't seem to be able to remember why he wrote what he did

Terrible proff, strays from topic at hand, refuses to explain in-depth when students are not comprehending, prefers to say: and........and........? horrible individual. does not give helpful feedback, writes like a doctor, makes lectures extremely personal at times, avoid if you want to LEARN!!!
AWESOME teacher! Motivating, entertaining, inspiring... I had a great time in his class!
Still the best Prof.I miss you, Prof. Meade.I hope I become as good a Prof as you were.

Great lecturer and instilled confidence in bridging students, but gave maddeningly little feedback on papers that were basically the entire course grades.  How can I improve my writing with "80%.  Good." on my paper?  Overall I thought he was a great introduction to UofT.

He was the best ( and first)Prof I had, way back in 1999, in the Pre U Lit Class. if every Prof had been as good as him,( Reibentanz, you listening?) I would be very happy. i hope he's still there, teaching eager young Minds.
If all Prof's were as pasionate and approchable as Meade, I would be a happy student.

He was understanding, made the transition into UofT less intimidating, and talked a lot about Jesus. The scope of the course is pretty narrow. We covered many different works but analysed them with the same point of view/theme.
Excellent prof. Very funny. Has a real passion for Literature. Very inspiring.
